# Plan: Extend exclusion list with additional low/medium cost types

## Context
A real scan against dev (50 distinct resource types) revealed the current exclusion list is too narrow — free/config-only types are still showing up as noise and drowning out actionable findings. Most egregious: `batch:job-definition` has 44,333 rows, all of which are versioned config objects with zero cost. Purpose of this change: prune the reported list down to types that actually drive cost, so the report becomes useful for tagging compliance.

## Scope
Single file change in `lambda/untagged-reporter/src/scanner.py` — extend `_DEFAULT_EXCLUDED_RESOURCE_TYPES` (currently ~55 entries) with the additional types below. No behaviour change beyond the expanded set; the post-filter code path in `_run_query` already supports this.

